<item>
            <title>[SOLR-9699] CoreStatus requests can fail if executed during a core reload</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-9699</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;CoreStatus requests delegate some of their response down to a core&apos;s IndexWriter.  If the core is being reloaded, then there&apos;s a race between these calls and the IndexWriter being closed, which can lead to the request failing with an AlreadyClosedException.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="13016182">SOLR-9699</key>
            <summary>CoreStatus requests can fail if executed during a core reload</summary>
